<br>
These days with a good break group I dont believe in just trying to get to the camp wihtout aggro.  I find aggro useful generally.<br>
<br>
You want to kill the mobs.  Thats why even if you have aggro, I say bring the mobs in.  Dont die.  Bring them to the camp.<br>
<br>
I do suppose it does depend on how good your tanks are.  But in general I find its not hard to find mobs with only 18 or so people in West Camp.  As long as your using /assist it doesnt really matter either.  Only the enchanter needs to know what mobs are in camp.  Since usually its the enchanter calling the shots in regard to which mob to kill next too.<br>
<br>
And yeah, the imps do shadowstep.  I find this more an annoyance than anything else though.  With 18 people, 15 of whom can engage in combat, I find they die fast these days.  Hell, as long as everything is mostly mez'd and your people are doing /assist right, the clerics can nuke too to help your DPS.<br>
<br>
And if you are fighting inside West Camp as you should be, shadowstep wont toss you anywhere really dangerous.  You might get another wanderer or two, but its all good.  As you are there to kill wanderers after all.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, and another thing.<br>
<br>
I have 1 easy way of making sure people use /assist and do not over aggro.<br>
<br>
As you might have remembered, when I was running KCoG Planar Raids, if a group didnt assist or got aggro, I'd simply remove the healers from that group.  There is nothing like taking the healers out to get melee's to start watching their aggro.<br>
<br>
More importantly, if you have more than 3 groups, you dont really need healers in each group.  Only the MA and SA and Command group really need healers.  For the other groups, the healer is nothing more than another DPS class really as they should never get hit.<br>
<br>
But then again, I dont believe in playing it too safe.  I believe in going in, using good tactics, and kicking ass.  I dont use perfect groups, I dont care about ever getting them.  I just care about clearing the zone.  heh.<br>
<br>
